      <div xml:id="NA282-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">ciṟaippuṟamākat tōḻi ceṟippaṟivuṟīi varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante urged for marriage by informing of [HER] confinement when [HE] was behind the fence.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA282">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            tōṭamai ceṟippi ṉilaṅkuvaḷai ñekiḻak</l>
<l>            kōṭēn talku lavvari vāṭa</l>
<l>            naṉṉutaṟ pāya paṭarmali yarunōy</l>
<l>            kātalar ṟantamai yaṟiyā tuṇartta</l>
<l>            vaṇaṅkuṟu kaḻaṅkiṉ mutuvāy vēlaṉ </l>
<l>            kiḷaviyiṟ ṟaṇiyi ṉaṉṟumaṉ cāra</l>
<l>            lakilcuṭu kāṉava ṉuvalcuṭu kamaḻpukai</l>
<l>            yāṭumaḻai maṅkuliṉ maṟaikku</l>
<l>            nāṭukeḻu veṟpaṉō ṭamaintanan toṭarpē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Good, certainly, if by the word</l>
<l rend="indent">of the spear-bearer of ancient truth, with awe-inspiring(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">aṇaṅku uṟu</term>: or "bothersome"?</note> molucca beans,</l>
<l rend="indent">who has informed without knowing it of [our] lover’s having given [it],</l>
<l>the difficult pain abounding in affliction would be alleviated,</l>
<l rend="indent3">while [pallor] spreads on [my] good forehead,</l>
<l rend="indent3">while those lines are fading on [my] hip with eminent rounds,</l>
<l rend="indent3">while tight(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ceṟippiṉ</term>: what is precisely expressed here that would not be contained in the simple attribute <term xml:lang="ta">ceṟi</term>? "bangles of tightness" = of the tight type?</note> shining bangles attached in a group become loose</l>
<l rend="indent">– because of our attachment that was settled with the man from a land of</l>
<l rend="indent">mountains, where the fragrant smoke of foliage burned by the forest man</l>
<l rend="indent">who burns eaglewood hides the slope like a dancing rain cloud.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
